          "username": "cl778h"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-14 22:41:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI see little value adding +1 to a change that failed verification. Checking it locally now.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "8d0289810bb3b4ed83c713d94f06406c5ac94908",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 681,
          "name": "Chris Lott",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "cl778h@att.com",
          "username": "cl778h"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-14 22:45:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nHere's the relevant error:\n\n15:48:42 jenkins_jobs.errors.JenkinsJobsException: container-public-registry parameter missing to format {container-public-registry}\n\nThe template you invoked requires the config parameter container-public-registry. Here's a block of examples from Acumos that live in jjb/defaults.jjb:\n\n    # Nexus3 docker registries\n    container-public-registry: nexus3.acumos.org:10001\n    container-snapshot-registry: nexus3.acumos.org:10003\n    container-staging-registry:  nexus3.acumos.org:10004\n    # the quotes here are REQUIRED\n    container-push-registry: '{container-staging-registry}'\n\nIt seems strange to me, but I guess there's a chance that you just might be the first person to use these global-jjb templates, so nobody extended the defaults file yet.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "fb62b7875bd9aa7b8af4d95822d57b1b67d929ed",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 515,
          "name": "Tommy Carpenter",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": null,
          "username": "tommycarpenter"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-15 00:18:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n> \n> Here's the relevant error:\n> \n> 15:48:42 jenkins_jobs.errors.JenkinsJobsException: container-public-registry parameter missing to format {container-public-registry}\n> \n> The template you invoked requires the config parameter container-public-registry. Here's a block of examples from Acumos that live in jjb/defaults.jjb:\n> \n>     # Nexus3 docker registries\n>     container-public-registry: nexus3.acumos.org:10001\n>     container-snapshot-registry: nexus3.acumos.org:10003\n>     container-staging-registry:  nexus3.acumos.org:10004\n>     # the quotes here are REQUIRED\n>     container-push-registry: '{container-staging-registry}'\n> \n> It seems strange to me, but I guess there's a chance that you just might be the first person to use these global-jjb templates, so nobody extended the defaults file yet.\n\nWhen you say \"the first person to use these global-jjb templates\", what do you mean exactly?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "13c648bc06c924d7ade54c0bc3d782870635411d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 681,
          "name": "Chris Lott",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "cl778h@att.com",
          "username": "cl778h"
        },
